The paper deals with adversarial examples in the context of open set recognition, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new approach for generating adversarial examples, which involves working with features and optimizing for retrieval rather than classification. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (machine learning), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), and cs.CR (cryptography and security). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on two datasets commonly used in CV research, Market-1501 and CUB-200-2011, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.MM (multimedia).
